{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":720,"text":"People have been using media\nto talk about sex for a long time."},{"time":5600,"text":"Love letters, phone sex, racy Polaroids."},{"time":9480,"text":"There's even a story of a girl who eloped\nwith a man that she met over the telegraph"},{"time":15560,"text":"in 1886."},{"time":18560,"text":"Today we have sexting,\nand I am a sexting expert."},{"time":23680,"text":"Not an expert sexter."},{"time":26800,"text":"Though, I do know what this means --\nI think you do too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"[it's a penis]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36360,"text":"I have been studying sexting since\nthe media attention to it began in 2008."},{"time":42720,"text":"I wrote a book on the moral\npanic about sexting."},{"time":45720,"text":"And here's what I found:"},{"time":47360,"text":"most people are worrying\nabout the wrong thing."},{"time":50600,"text":"They're trying to just prevent\nsexting from happening entirely."},{"time":54800,"text":"But let me ask you this:"},{"time":56360,"text":"As long as it's completely consensual,\nwhat's the problem with sexting?"},{"time":61240,"text":"People are into all sorts of things\nthat you may not be into,"},{"time":65280,"text":"like blue cheese or cilantro."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70600,"text":"Sexting is certainly risky,\nlike anything that's fun,"},{"time":74760,"text":"but as long as you're not sending an image\nto someone who doesn't want to receive it,"},{"time":81480,"text":"there's no harm."},{"time":83280,"text":"What I do think is a serious problem"},{"time":85920,"text":"is when people share\nprivate images of others"},{"time":89200,"text":"without their permission."},{"time":91360,"text":"And instead of worrying about sexting,"},{"time":93720,"text":"what I think we need to do\nis think a lot more about digital privacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98880,"text":"The key is consent."},{"time":101680,"text":"Right now most people\nare thinking about sexting"},{"time":105000,"text":"without really thinking\nabout consent at all."},{"time":108400,"text":"Did you know that we currently\ncriminalize teen sexting?"},{"time":113400,"text":"It can be a crime because\nit counts as child pornography,"},{"time":116880,"text":"if there's an image of someone under 18,"},{"time":119760,"text":"and it doesn't even matter"},{"time":121120,"text":"if they took that image of themselves\nand shared it willingly."},{"time":125800,"text":"So we end up with this\nbizarre legal situation"},{"time":128800,"text":"where two 17-year-olds\ncan legally have sex in most US states"},{"time":133360,"text":"but they can't photograph it."},{"time":136560,"text":"Some states have also tried\npassing sexting misdemeanor laws"},{"time":140840,"text":"but these laws repeat the same problem"},{"time":143880,"text":"because they still\nmake consensual sexting illegal."},{"time":148520,"text":"It doesn't make sense"},{"time":149800,"text":"to try to ban all sexting\nto try to address privacy violations."},{"time":154560,"text":"This is kind of like saying,"},{"time":156080,"text":"let's solve the problem of date rape\nby just making dating completely illegal."},{"time":163120,"text":"Most teens don't get arrested for sexting,\nbut can you guess who does?"},{"time":168520,"text":"It's often teens who are disliked\nby their partner's parents."},{"time":173520,"text":"And this can be because of class bias,\nracism or homophobia."},{"time":178960,"text":"Most prosecutors are,\nof course, smart enough"},{"time":181760,"text":"not to use child pornography charges\nagainst teenagers, but some do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187720,"text":"According to researchers\nat the University of New Hampshire"},{"time":191400,"text":"seven percent of all child pornography\npossession arrests are teens,"},{"time":197080,"text":"sexting consensually with other teens."},{"time":201480,"text":"Child pornography is a serious crime,"},{"time":204040,"text":"but it's just not\nthe same thing as teen sexting."},{"time":209040,"text":"Parents and educators\nare also responding to sexting"},{"time":212480,"text":"without really thinking\ntoo much about consent."},{"time":215640,"text":"Their message to teens is often:\njust don't do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220200,"text":"And I totally get it --\nthere are serious legal risks"},{"time":223720,"text":"and of course, that potential\nfor privacy violations."},{"time":227400,"text":"And when you were a teen,"},{"time":228680,"text":"I'm sure you did exactly\nas you were told, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233440,"text":"You're probably thinking,\nmy kid would never sext."},{"time":236920,"text":"And that's true, your little angel\nmay not be sexting"},{"time":240400,"text":"because only 33 percent"},{"time":243560,"text":"of 16- and 17-year-olds are sexting."},{"time":247200,"text":"But, sorry, by the time they're older,\nodds are they will be sexting."},{"time":251840,"text":"Every study I've seen puts the rate\nabove 50 percent for 18- to 24-year-olds."},{"time":258720,"text":"And most of the time, nothing goes wrong."},{"time":261800,"text":"People ask me all the time things like,\nisn't sexting just so dangerous, though?"},{"time":267200,"text":"It's like you wouldn't\nleave your wallet on a park bench"},{"time":270800,"text":"and you expect it's going to get stolen\nif you do that, right?"},{"time":274880,"text":"Here's how I think about it:"},{"time":276360,"text":"sexting is like leaving your wallet\nat your boyfriend's house."},{"time":280320,"text":"If you come back the next day"},{"time":282120,"text":"and all the money is just gone,"},{"time":285040,"text":"you really need to dump that guy."},{"time":287690,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":291360,"text":"So instead of criminalizing sexting"},{"time":293720,"text":"to try to prevent\nthese privacy violations,"},{"time":296360,"text":"instead we need to make consent central"},{"time":299680,"text":"to how we think about the circulation\nof our private information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304480,"text":"Every new media technology\nraises privacy concerns."},{"time":308760,"text":"In fact, in the US the very first\nmajor debates about privacy"},{"time":313400,"text":"were in response to technologies\nthat were relatively new at the time."},{"time":317920,"text":"In the late 1800s,\npeople were worried about cameras,"},{"time":321840,"text":"which were just suddenly\nmore portable than ever before,"},{"time":325320,"text":"and newspaper gossip columns."},{"time":327840,"text":"They were worried that the camera\nwould capture information about them,"},{"time":331680,"text":"take it out of context\nand widely disseminate it."},{"time":335240,"text":"Does this sound familiar?"},{"time":336880,"text":"It's exactly what we're worrying about\nnow with social media and drone cameras,"},{"time":341760,"text":"and, of course, sexting."},{"time":343920,"text":"And these fears about technology,"},{"time":346160,"text":"they make sense"},{"time":347400,"text":"because technologies\ncan amplify and bring out"},{"time":350840,"text":"our worst qualities and behaviors."},{"time":354160,"text":"But there are solutions."},{"time":356560,"text":"And we've been here before\nwith a dangerous new technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360720,"text":"In 1908, Ford introduced the Model T car."},{"time":364520,"text":"Traffic fatality rates were rising."},{"time":367120,"text":"It was a serious problem --\nit looks so safe, right?"},{"time":372080,"text":"Our first response\nwas to try to change drivers' behavior,"},{"time":376080,"text":"so we developed speed limits\nand enforced them through fines."},{"time":380240,"text":"But over the following decades,"},{"time":382120,"text":"we started to realize the technology\nof the car itself is not just neutral."},{"time":387640,"text":"We could design the car to make it safer."},{"time":390880,"text":"So in the 1920s, we got\nshatter-resistant windshields."},{"time":394360,"text":"In the 1950s, seat belts."},{"time":396880,"text":"And in the 1990s, airbags."},{"time":400440,"text":"All three of these areas:"},{"time":402840,"text":"laws, individuals and industry\ncame together over time"},{"time":407640,"text":"to help solve the problem\nthat a new technology causes."},{"time":411440,"text":"And we can do the same thing\nwith digital privacy."},{"time":415160,"text":"Of course, it comes back to consent."},{"time":418360,"text":"Here's the idea."},{"time":419600,"text":"Before anyone can distribute\nyour private information,"},{"time":423440,"text":"they should have to get your permission."},{"time":426240,"text":"This idea of affirmative consent\ncomes from anti-rape activists"},{"time":431080,"text":"who tell us that we need consent\nfor every sexual act."},{"time":434880,"text":"And we have really high standards\nfor consent in a lot of other areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439480,"text":"Think about having surgery."},{"time":441360,"text":"Your doctor has to make sure"},{"time":443000,"text":"that you are meaningfully and knowingly\nconsenting to that medical procedure."},{"time":447520,"text":"This is not the type of consent\nlike with an iTunes Terms of Service"},{"time":451240,"text":"where you just scroll to the bottom\nand you're like, agree, agree, whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457160,"text":"If we think more about consent,\nwe can have better privacy laws."},{"time":462440,"text":"Right now, we just don't have\nthat many protections."},{"time":465880,"text":"If your ex-husband or your ex-wife\nis a terrible person,"},{"time":469480,"text":"they can take your nude photos\nand upload them to a porn site."},{"time":473720,"text":"It can be really hard\nto get those images taken down."},{"time":476960,"text":"And in a lot of states,"},{"time":478200,"text":"you're actually better off\nif you took the images of yourself"},{"time":482040,"text":"because then you can\nfile a copyright claim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487400,"text":"Right now, if someone\nviolates your privacy,"},{"time":490400,"text":"whether that's an individual\nor a company or the NSA,"},{"time":495280,"text":"you can try filing a lawsuit,"},{"time":498040,"text":"though you may not be successful"},{"time":500200,"text":"because many courts assume\nthat digital privacy is just impossible."},{"time":505000,"text":"So they're not willing\nto punish anyone for violating it."},{"time":509200,"text":"I still hear people\nasking me all the time,"},{"time":512120,"text":"isn't a digital image somehow blurring\nthe line between public and private"},{"time":517440,"text":"because it's digital, right?"},{"time":519600,"text":"No! No!"},{"time":520960,"text":"Everything digital\nis not just automatically public."},{"time":524320,"text":"That doesn't make any sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526240,"text":"As NYU legal scholar\nHelen Nissenbaum tells us,"},{"time":529760,"text":"we have laws and policies and norms"},{"time":532400,"text":"that protect all kinds\nof information that's private,"},{"time":535560,"text":"and it doesn't make a difference\nif it's digital or not."},{"time":539000,"text":"All of your health records are digitized"},{"time":541680,"text":"but your doctor can't\njust share them with anyone."},{"time":544840,"text":"All of your financial information\nis held in digital databases,"},{"time":549320,"text":"but your credit card company can't\njust post your purchase history online."},{"time":555080,"text":"Better laws could help address\nprivacy violations after they happen,"},{"time":560560,"text":"but one of the easiest things\nwe can all do is make personal changes"},{"time":564960,"text":"to help protect each other's privacy."},{"time":568360,"text":"We're always told that privacy"},{"time":570280,"text":"is our own, sole,\nindividual responsibility."},{"time":573360,"text":"We're told, constantly monitor\nand update your privacy settings."},{"time":577640,"text":"We're told, never share anything\nyou wouldn't want the entire world to see."},{"time":583400,"text":"This doesn't make sense."},{"time":584640,"text":"Digital media are social environments"},{"time":587640,"text":"and we share things\nwith people we trust all day, every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592760,"text":"As Princeton researcher\nJanet Vertesi argues,"},{"time":595760,"text":"our data and our privacy,\nthey're not just personal,"},{"time":599800,"text":"they're actually interpersonal."},{"time":602400,"text":"And so one thing you can do\nthat's really easy"},{"time":605680,"text":"is just start asking for permission before\nyou share anyone else's information."},{"time":610800,"text":"If you want to post a photo\nof someone online, ask for permission."},{"time":615360,"text":"If you want to forward an email thread,"},{"time":617840,"text":"ask for permission."},{"time":619240,"text":"And if you want to share\nsomeone's nude selfie,"},{"time":622040,"text":"obviously, ask for permission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625560,"text":"These individual changes can really\nhelp us protect each other's privacy,"},{"time":630040,"text":"but we need technology companies\non board as well."},{"time":634360,"text":"These companies have very little\nincentive to help protect our privacy"},{"time":638880,"text":"because their business models\ndepend on us sharing everything"},{"time":642200,"text":"with as many people as possible."},{"time":645080,"text":"Right now, if I send you an image,"},{"time":647040,"text":"you can forward that\nto anyone that you want."},{"time":650160,"text":"But what if I got to decide\nif that image was forwardable or not?"},{"time":654440,"text":"This would tell you, you don't\nhave my permission to send this image out."},{"time":658520,"text":"We do this kind of thing all the time\nto protect copyright."},{"time":662680,"text":"If you buy an e-book, you can't just\nsend it out to as many people as you want."},{"time":667480,"text":"So why not try this with mobile phones?"},{"time":670960,"text":"What you can do is we can demand\nthat tech companies add these protections"},{"time":675760,"text":"to our devices and our platforms\nas the default."},{"time":679520,"text":"After all, you can choose\nthe color of your car,"},{"time":682960,"text":"but the airbags are always standard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688080,"text":"If we don't think more\nabout digital privacy and consent,"},{"time":691920,"text":"there can be serious consequences."},{"time":695360,"text":"There was a teenager from Ohio --"},{"time":697640,"text":"let's call her Jennifer,\nfor the sake of her privacy."},{"time":701120,"text":"She shared nude photos of herself\nwith her high school boyfriend,"},{"time":704720,"text":"thinking she could trust him."},{"time":707720,"text":"Unfortunately, he betrayed her"},{"time":709680,"text":"and sent her photos\naround the entire school."},{"time":712680,"text":"Jennifer was embarrassed and humiliated,"},{"time":716800,"text":"but instead of being compassionate,\nher classmates harassed her."},{"time":720960,"text":"They called her a slut and a whore"},{"time":722840,"text":"and they made her life miserable."},{"time":725360,"text":"Jennifer started missing school\nand her grades dropped."},{"time":729520,"text":"Ultimately, Jennifer decided\nto end her own life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734720,"text":"Jennifer did nothing wrong."},{"time":737440,"text":"All she did was share a nude photo"},{"time":739720,"text":"with someone she thought\nthat she could trust."},{"time":742560,"text":"And yet our laws tell her"},{"time":745200,"text":"that she committed a horrible crime\nequivalent to child pornography."},{"time":749920,"text":"Our gender norms tell her"},{"time":751440,"text":"that by producing\nthis nude image of herself,"},{"time":754680,"text":"she somehow did the most\nhorrible, shameful thing."},{"time":758400,"text":"And when we assume that privacy\nis impossible in digital media,"},{"time":762640,"text":"we completely write off and excuse\nher boyfriend's bad, bad behavior."},{"time":769200,"text":"People are still saying all the time\nto victims of privacy violations,"},{"time":774960,"text":"\"What were you thinking?"},{"time":776240,"text":"You should have never sent that image.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":779640,"text":"If you're trying to figure out\nwhat to say instead, try this."},{"time":784160,"text":"Imagine you've run into your friend\nwho broke their leg skiing."},{"time":788240,"text":"They took a risk to do something fun,\nand it didn't end well."},{"time":792840,"text":"But you're probably\nnot going to be the jerk who says,"},{"time":795400,"text":"\"Well, I guess you shouldn't\nhave gone skiing then.\""},{"time":800080,"text":"If we think more about consent,"},{"time":802240,"text":"we can see that victims\nof privacy violations"},{"time":805520,"text":"deserve our compassion,"},{"time":807280,"text":"not criminalization, shaming,\nharassment or punishment."},{"time":812440,"text":"We can support victims,\nand we can prevent some privacy violations"},{"time":816960,"text":"by making these legal,\nindividual and technological changes."},{"time":821840,"text":"Because the problem is not sexting,\nthe issue is digital privacy."},{"time":827680,"text":"And one solution is consent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830680,"text":"So the next time a victim\nof a privacy violation comes up to you,"},{"time":835280,"text":"instead of blaming them,\nlet's do this instead:"},{"time":838040,"text":"let's shift our ideas\nabout digital privacy,"},{"time":841480,"text":"and let's respond with compassion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844680,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}